C/2022 E3 is a comet that was discovered in the year 2022. Last time it was spotted we were Neanderthals fifty thousand years ago!

 I've been attempting to get a decent photo of it for the last 2 weeks, braving some extreme cold, technical issues, moon issues I finally got something I am reasonably happy with. Mars is on the left C/2022 E3 aka green comet on the right.

Big thanks to @j.wilsonphotos for all the help :) 

Shot on a #nikonz6 and #nikon200500. 5 1minute exposures at iso 1600 f6.3 using a sky adventurer pro tracker.

Great Horned Owlet

Went out for a quick evening stroll to see what kind of wildlife we could find. after about 20 minutes I came to realize the warblers I was there to photograph were not very active, a bit discouraged I photographed some yellow rumps that were pretty close to pass some time.

 Then to my surprise @kmb.pebbles spots a great Horned owl about 50 feet away! Definitely made up for the otherwise not very eventful walk 🙂

Photographed on a Nikon #d500 and Nikon #nikon200500

Red Morph Screech Owl

Behold the majestic beauty of this Red Morph Screech Owl, adorned in vibrant hues that ignite the spirit. Its crimson plumage dances with the setting sun, casting a spell of enchantment upon the forest. With piercing golden eyes that mirror the wisdom of ages, it emerges as a symbol of resilience and adaptability. In its graceful flight, it whispers ancient tales, echoing the harmony between nature and its inhabitants. Witness the splendor of this elusive creature, a captivating marvel of nature's palette. Let its vibrant presence inspire us to embrace our own uniqueness, celebrating the kaleidoscope of life's colors.

Thanks chat gpt for the caption 😆

Shot on a Nikon #d500 lens Nikon #nikon200500

Low Point lighthouse 

This is one of the earliest and most important lighthouses in Nova Scotia, built in 1832 this has been guiding Mariners into Sydney harbour for almost two centuries!

Was hoping for some clear skies that night, but more than happy with the moody overall feel this image has created.
.
.
.
#novascotia #lighthouse #lowpointlighthouse #nikon20mm #nikonusa #nikoncanada #my3leggedthing #novascotiatourism #nightphotography #ShareCanGeo #canadiancreatives #nikonz6

Louisbourg Lighthouse 

This photo uses the last 5000 years of navigational aids to help the Mariners cross the Atlantic ocean. First one being the stars- people have been using stars  dating back to  3000bc to help navigate. Second is the lighthouse, the first lighthouse was built 280bc in Egypt. Third is modern day GPS, I used an app called #photopills to plan this shot months in advance knowing where the milky way would be and the moon phases certainly makes modern technology a joy to use sometimes.
.

Milky Way along the Cape Breton Coast

There's an undeniable magic in gazing upon the night sky along the East coast. The vast expanse above, adorned with countless stars, never fails to evoke a sense of wonder. The sheer solitude of wandering through the night, with only the rhythmic orchestra of waves crashing against the shore as your companion, creates a profound and unforgettable experience. It's during these moments that you realize the beauty of finding solace in nature's embrace, far away from the hustle and bustle of daily life.
.

Hocking Hills Canyon Hike

Chasing golden light through the enchanting canyons of Hocking Hills, where canyons whisper tales of ancient beauty. Each step, a dance with nature's wonders. Lost in the embrace of towering cliffs, discovering the secrets carved by time.

Gear Used

Nikon z6 with 20mm f1.8

#hockinghills #hockinghillsstatepark #nikon #discoverohio #naturalohio #hikeohio #osprey #longexposure

The Hocking hills area really is a gem, always blows my mind that this place is in Ohio. Checks off all the vibe boxes with its lush mossy greens and sandstone cliffs. 

Gear used Nikon z6 and 85mm 1.8
Exif f8 iso100 1/2 second shutter with 5 stop nd filter.

Ash Cave 🪨💧⛰️

The overall scale of Ash Cave is pretty incredible, We were lucky to spend a few hours in the early morning watching the golden light paint the walls above without a sole around. This location has it all,a waterfall cascading over the cliffs above to sand stone caves. 

I photographed this using a fish eye lens which almost gets a 180 degree field of view.
